............................................................................................................................................................................ 111 iii 2016 COPS Office Tribal Resources Grant Program (TRGP) Award Owner’s Manual Getting Started\nCongratulations on receiving an award from the U.S. Department of Justice, Office of Community Oriented\nPolicing Services (COPS Office). The 2016 COPS Office Tribal Resources Grant Program (TRGP) provides funding\ndirectly to federally recognized tribal jurisdictions with established law enforcement agencies. TRGP was\ndesigned to expand the implementation of community policing and meet the most serious needs of law\nenforcement in tribal communities through a broadened comprehensive program. In Fiscal Year 2010, the U.S. Department of Justice (DOJ) issued a single Coordinated Tribal Assistance Solicitation\n(CTAS) that encompassed the department’s available Tribal Government–specific award programs. CTAS\nenabled each tribe to submit a single application for available award funding according to the tribes’ needs."
